1 Abstract

Brain-computer interfaces (BCIs) are advancing from experimental medical devices toward consumer technology, yet their security frameworks remain rooted entirely in classical computing paradigms. This paper introduces the QIF â€” Quantum Indeterministic Framework for Neural Security (pronounced â€œCHIEFâ€), a 7-band symmetric hourglass (3-1-3) security architecture derived from neuroscience and quantum physics that addresses a critical blind spot: quantum-scale phenomena at the electrode-tissue interface that may be invisible to classical detection, if operationally significant.

We present the QI equation in two complementary forms â€” an additive engineering model for BCI practitioners and a tensor-product theoretical model for physicists â€” that unify 21 established equations from classical physics, neuroscience, and quantum mechanics into a single security metric. The framework maps 8 open questions in quantum neuroscience as tunable parameters rather than fixed assumptions, making the equation future-proof by design.

We identify six novel contributions not found in prior literature, including quantum biometrics via ion channel tunneling profiles and Zeno-BCI stabilization. Five testable experimental predictions are proposed for empirical validation.

12 Encyclopedia of Terms

NoteClick to expand full encyclopedia

Action Potential â€” An electrical pulse that travels along a nerve cell. Duration ~1-2 ms, speed 1-100 m/s. Modeled by Hodgkin-Huxley equation.

BCI (Brain-Computer Interface) â€” A device creating direct communication between brain and computer. Example: Neuralink N1 (1024 electrodes, 19.3-20 kHz sampling).

Bell States â€” Maximally entangled qubit pairs: |Phi+> = (1/sqrt(2))(|00> + |11>). Used in QKD protocols (E91).

Born Rule â€” P(x) = |psi(x)|^2. The fundamental rule connecting quantum math to measurement probability.

Coherence (Neural) â€” Synchronized neural oscillations. High coherence = effective communication. QIFâ€™s Cs quantifies this.

Coherence (Quantum) â€” Ability to exist in superposition. Fragile â€” destroyed by decoherence.

Davydov Soliton â€” Quantum quasiparticle propagating along protein alpha-helices. Can trigger synaptic vesicle release via tunneling through SNARE complexes. QIF identifies as attack vector.

Decoherence â€” Loss of quantum properties through environmental interaction. Time constant: tau_D (disputed: 10â»Â¹Â³ s to Hours).

Entanglement â€” Non-classical correlation between quantum particles. Measuring one instantly affects the other. NOT faster-than-light communication.

Fisherâ€™s Posner Molecules â€” Hypothesis: Ca9(PO4)6 nanoclusters sustain entanglement for hours via P-31 nuclear spins. Speculative, unverified.

Groverâ€™s Algorithm â€” O(sqrt(N)) quantum search. Provably optimal. Halves effective key lengths for symmetric crypto.

Heisenberg Uncertainty â€” DxDp >= hbar/2. Cannot simultaneously know exact position and momentum. Guarantees eavesdropper detection.

No-Cloning Theorem â€” Impossible to copy an arbitrary unknown quantum state. Guarantees quantum-secured signals canâ€™t be replicated.

Quantum Biometric (Novel) â€” Ion channel tunneling profile as unforgeable identity. Unique per person, unclonable by physics.

Robertson-Schrodinger â€” Generalized uncertainty: exact equality for qubits. QIF can compute indeterminacy exactly.

Shorâ€™s Algorithm â€” O(n^3) quantum factoring. RSA-2048: ~8 hours / 20M noisy qubits (Gidney & EkerÃ¥ 2019, arXiv:1905.09749).

tau_D (Decoherence Time) â€” How long quantum effects persist. Greek tau = time constant, D = decoherence. QIF treats as tunable parameter.

Von Neumann Entropy â€” S(rho) = -Tr(rho ln rho). Quantum uncertainty measure. Subsystem can exceed total (entanglement signature).

Zeno Effect (Quantum) â€” Frequent measurement freezes quantum evolution. QIF hypothesis: BCIâ€™s 1kHz+ sampling may stabilize quantum states.

```{python}
#| label: fig-hourglass
#| fig-cap: "QIF v3.0 â€” 7-Band Hourglass Architecture (3-1-3 symmetric). Width represents state space. Narrowest at I0 (measurement collapses possibilities)."

zone_colors = {z_id: z["color"] for z_id, z in ZONES.items()}

n = len(BANDS)

for i, band in enumerate(BANDS):
    y = n - 1 - i
    color = zone_colors[band["zone"]]
    alpha = 0.95 if band["id"] == "I0" else 0.8

    width = 0.2 + band["hourglass_width"] * 0.7
    x_offset = (1.0 - width) / 2

                          edgecolor='white', linewidth=2, zorder=2)

    ax.text(0.5, y + 0.42, f"{band['id']}: {band['name']}",
            ha='center', va='center', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold', color='white', zorder=3)

    qi_lo, qi_hi = band["qi_range"]
    qi_text = f"QI {qi_lo}â€“{qi_hi}" if qi_hi > 0 else "QI â‰ˆ 0"
    ax.text(0.5 + width / 2 + 0.15, y + 0.42, qi_text,
            ha='left', va='center', fontsize=8, color='gray', zorder=3)

# Zone labels â€” dynamic
neural_ys = [n - 1 - i for i, b in enumerate(BANDS) if b["zone"] == "neural"]

silicon_ys = [n - 1 - i for i, b in enumerate(BANDS) if b["zone"] == "silicon"]
```

### Von Neumann Entropy Non-Monotonicity

```{python}
#| label: fig-entropy
```

```{python}
#| label: fig-scenarios

fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 6))

for name, scenario in SCENARIOS.items():
    if name in ('quantum_regime_short', 'decoherence_boundary'):
        continue
    data = generate_custom_signals(scenario)
    result = full_qi_assessment(
        phases=data['phases'], transport_probs=data['transport_probs'],
        amplitudes=data['amplitudes'], t=1e-6, tau_d=1e-5)
    names.append(scenario.name.replace(' ', '\n'))
    coherences.append(result.coherence)

    c2s.append(result.qi_score_c2)
```

## Encyclopedia of Terms

::: {.callout-note collapse="true" title="Click to expand full encyclopedia"}

**Action Potential** â€” An electrical pulse that travels along a nerve cell. Duration ~1-2 ms, speed 1-100 m/s. Modeled by Hodgkin-Huxley equation.

**BCI (Brain-Computer Interface)** â€” A device creating direct communication between brain and computer. Example: Neuralink N1 (`{python} NEURALINK_N1['electrodes']` electrodes, `{python} NEURALINK_N1['sampling_rate_khz']` kHz sampling).

**Bell States** â€” Maximally entangled qubit pairs: |Phi+> = (1/sqrt(2))(|00> + |11>). Used in QKD protocols (E91).

**Born Rule** â€” P(x) = |psi(x)|^2. The fundamental rule connecting quantum math to measurement probability.

**Coherence (Neural)** â€” Synchronized neural oscillations. High coherence = effective communication. QIF's Cs quantifies this.

**Coherence (Quantum)** â€” Ability to exist in superposition. Fragile â€” destroyed by decoherence.

**Davydov Soliton** â€” Quantum quasiparticle propagating along protein alpha-helices. Can trigger synaptic vesicle release via tunneling through SNARE complexes. QIF identifies as attack vector.

**Decoherence** â€” Loss of quantum properties through environmental interaction. Time constant: tau_D (disputed: `{python} DECOHERENCE_CAMPS[0]['label']` to `{python} DECOHERENCE_CAMPS[2]['label']`).

**Entanglement** â€” Non-classical correlation between quantum particles. Measuring one instantly affects the other. NOT faster-than-light communication.

**Fisher's Posner Molecules** â€” Hypothesis: Ca9(PO4)6 nanoclusters sustain entanglement for hours via P-31 nuclear spins. Speculative, unverified.

**Grover's Algorithm** â€” O(sqrt(N)) quantum search. Provably optimal. Halves effective key lengths for symmetric crypto.

**Heisenberg Uncertainty** â€” DxDp >= hbar/2. Cannot simultaneously know exact position and momentum. Guarantees eavesdropper detection.

**No-Cloning Theorem** â€” Impossible to copy an arbitrary unknown quantum state. Guarantees quantum-secured signals can't be replicated.

**Quantum Biometric** (Novel) â€” Ion channel tunneling profile as unforgeable identity. Unique per person, unclonable by physics.

**Robertson-Schrodinger** â€” Generalized uncertainty: exact equality for qubits. QIF can compute indeterminacy exactly.

**Shor's Algorithm** â€” O(n^3) quantum factoring. RSA-2048: `{python} QUANTUM_THREATS[0]['value']` (`{python} QUANTUM_THREATS[0]['source']`).

**tau_D (Decoherence Time)** â€” How long quantum effects persist. Greek tau = time constant, D = decoherence. QIF treats as tunable parameter.

**Von Neumann Entropy** â€” S(rho) = -Tr(rho ln rho). Quantum uncertainty measure. Subsystem can exceed total (entanglement signature).

**Zeno Effect (Quantum)** â€” Frequent measurement freezes quantum evolution. QIF hypothesis: BCI's 1kHz+ sampling may stabilize quantum states.

:::
